{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-11-01","name":"Anne Giffard","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Anne Giffard","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Anne"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"Giffard"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"Annie Grifford","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1440–1507","fullLifespan":"1440–Aft 1507","birthDate":"+1440","birthPlace":{"address":"Bradwell, Gloucestershire, England","geo":{"latitude":51.7325,"longitude":0.8896,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1507","deathPlace":{"address":"Madresfield, Worcestershire, England","geo":{"latitude":52.12604,"longitude":-2.2796,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"«b»Biography«/b»\nAnne Giffard was born in 1440 in Matson, Gloucestershire, England. She was the daughter and heiress of Nicholas Giffard, Squire of Matson, b. 1410 in Gloucestershire; and his 2nd wife, Margery (Dicleston) Giffard, b. 1414 in Besford, Worcestershire.\n\nShe married Thomas Lygon, Esq., of Great Malvern and Madresfield, Worcestershire, England, Knight of the shire for Worcestershire. Thomas Lygon, Esq., was born in about 1436. Their marriage took place around 1460 in Worcestershire.\n\n«b»Anne Giffardand Thomas Lygon had three children:«/b»\n1.) Jane Lygon b: 1464 in Madresfield, Worcester, England\n\n2.) Richard Lygon b: 1470 in Madresfield, Worcester, England\n\n3.) William Lygon b: 1478 in Arle Court / Madresfield, Worcester, England\n\nAnne (Giffard) Lygon died after 1507 at Madresfield, Worcestershire, England; that was the year Sir Thomas Lygon died and she was named in the Will.","sourceList":[{"title":"Legacy NFS Source: Ane Gifford - death: 1468; Madresfield, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom","sourceType":"LEGACY","sourceUri":"MMPG-R8Y"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1440","date":"1440","place":"Bradwell, Gloucestershire, England"},{"name":"Marriage","sources":"0","year":"1453","date":"1